HEADWORD: Concionator
<hw>Con"cio*na`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An haranguer of the people; a preacher.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Old Law)</fld> <def>A common councilman.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concionatory</ent>⟦br⟧
